Descends into a station, below street level through the gates, and lower, lines overhead, who knows how many levels? Trains flying invisible, pressed to the people of the underground feeling every movement of the bodies of warmth in transit over the rails. He changes further down, crowd converging at the top of the stairs, deeper into the mud bricks echoing metal on metal, white noise of footsteps rolling out with a rising whine into the subterranean network turning and maybe descending on a subtle incline he might be imagining.